forever SHAMPOO you pre-program movements in combination with AI that can evolve and learn from previous imputation which allows these robots to do what you see. You see how it can do a back flip now? Well with the information it attained from learning to do the flip it can use that information and apply it at later times to achieve a goal. It's similar to that other video they have uploaded of the robot slipping on the banana. It will learn from the error and use it at a later time for its own benefit. Think of it like this. I have an alphabet and I give you all the letters but you don't know how to spell and you don't know what words are. If I teach you words it's great and all but you still won't know how to make sentences as you don't know the context of words in combination with other words. You may get lucky and make a sentence that makes sense but not likely on the first try. That lucky part is where we exploit information since most learning algorithm are trial and error. Once in a while the program is right and makes a sentence that makes sense. It stores that information if it gets the right outcome. So that robot you seen fell on its face a thousand times before it did a back flip.
